feed.title: Arduino Rainwater Tank level 2m³
feed.description: This is a level measurement used to measure my rainwater tank the program is written for arduino and is developed by Joeri Gantois, Wim de Bonte and Erik de Cock. It works with a DFRobot URM V3.2 Ultrasonic Sensor .It sends a ultrasonic signal to the water and count the time between sending and receiving the signal. The lower the water the longer it takes to receive the sended signal. I downloaded the code (sketch) from http://www.jo3ri.be/arduino. Joeri helped me to finetune the arduino program so I can use it for my level measurement. I use the water to flush my toilets and for cleaning purposes. I use appox. 44m³ Rainwater a year. I want to use the program also to stop an (hydrofoor) pump if the level is too low. A valve should be activated so the toilets will be flushed with drinking water. The stopping of the pump en opening en closing of the valve has still to be programmed.
